03:22.272 --> 03:23.573
I can explain.

03:23.607 --> 03:26.342
You better fuckin'
explain yourself, motherfucker.

03:26.376 --> 03:27.810
Well, it was a long flight.

03:27.844 --> 03:29.478
You know, we got to talking.

03:29.512 --> 03:31.780
One thing led to another.

03:31.814 --> 03:33.514
What the fuck you talkin' about, man?

03:35.851 --> 03:37.017
I don't know, what the fuck
am I talkin' about?

03:37.051 --> 03:38.185
What the fuck am I talk--

03:38.219 --> 03:39.352
What the fuck are you talkin' about?

03:39.387 --> 03:40.987
I'm talkin' about the fact

03:41.022 --> 03:42.889
that you're always fuckin' late, man.

03:42.923 --> 03:44.223
Oh, all right.

03:44.258 --> 03:45.725
That's some real
passive-aggressive shit, right?

03:45.759 --> 03:46.893
You think your time is more valuable

03:46.927 --> 03:48.061
than my time, don't you?

03:48.096 --> 03:49.329
- Actually--
- I sense that shit, man.

03:49.364 --> 03:50.330
Actually, I don't.
I don't.

03:50.365 --> 03:52.166
But--but in a larger sense,

03:52.200 --> 03:54.135
my time will always be my time.

03:54.169 --> 03:55.970
So it will always mean
more to me personally.

03:56.005 --> 03:58.206
Ah, man, shut the fuck up
and buy a watch, nigga.

03:58.240 --> 03:59.207
A'ight.

03:59.242 --> 04:00.208
In the meantime, nigga,

04:00.243 --> 04:01.610
I need your help, Moody.

04:01.645 --> 04:04.146
How can I be of service, my liege?

04:04.181 --> 04:05.515
I got this piece of music here, right?

04:05.549 --> 04:08.517
[Playing slow ballad on piano]

04:26.770 --> 04:29.238
That is... mighty purty.

04:29.273 --> 04:31.541
It's like vintage Elton John there.

04:31.575 --> 04:33.610
Yeah, well, this bitch
ain't no fuckin' Bernie Taupin.

04:33.644 --> 04:35.178
That's why we can't
work together, Calvin.

04:35.213 --> 04:36.380
Because if I'm not sleeping with him,

04:36.414 --> 04:37.448
he's a total fucking asshole.

04:37.482 --> 04:38.782
Yeah, well, you know...

04:38.817 --> 04:40.418
She can't write not
fuckin' lyrics, yo.

04:40.452 --> 04:42.019
Just a pretty face
and a fuckin' smile.

04:42.053 --> 04:43.521
All right, all right, all right.

04:43.555 --> 04:44.889
Well, how can I help?

04:44.923 --> 04:46.924
Help the girl write
some fuckin' lyrics, man.

04:46.959 --> 04:48.392
Oh, no, no.

04:48.427 --> 04:51.862
I write books...
screenplays, emails, uh--

04:51.896 --> 04:53.030
Nigga, writin' is writin', man.

04:53.064 --> 04:55.165
- I don't.
- Help a brother out.

04:59.603 --> 05:01.071
Okay, I'll give it a shot.

05:01.105 --> 05:03.707
But we're gonna have
to get good and drunk first.

05:03.741 --> 05:06.342
See, now, that's the best
fuckin' idea I've heard all day.

05:06.377 --> 05:08.277
Let's go.

05:08.312 --> 05:09.546
All right, so where are we starting?

05:09.580 --> 05:10.780
I don't know.

05:10.815 --> 05:12.282
It's obviously a love song, right?

05:12.317 --> 05:14.451
So what rhymes with love?

05:14.485 --> 05:16.320
Dove, shove.

05:16.354 --> 05:18.989
"Did you just shove a dove
up my ass and call it love?"

05:19.023 --> 05:19.990
Done!

05:20.024 --> 05:22.092
Writing lyrics is easy.

05:22.126 --> 05:23.760
Next!

05:23.794 --> 05:25.128
Okay, the "no fun" face.

05:25.163 --> 05:26.363
What do you wanna write about?

05:26.397 --> 05:27.597
